        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "uja.ornl@gmail.com",
          "date": "2013-02-28 14:13:18.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-1718 llite: Restore NFS export for Lustre on early kernels",
        "message": "LU-1718 llite: Restore NFS export for Lustre on early kernels\n\nFor kernels at 2.6.18 or earlier and kernels at 3.0+ the\nstruct file_system_type changed the get_sb function to a\nnew function called mount which was different in that the\nvfsmount data was no longer passed in. The vfsmount data\nwas used by the llite layer for nfs export function called\nget_name to search for filp that was then used with the\nll_readdir method. The approach to solve this change was\nto go the route of btrfs and gfs2 to refactor some of the\nllite methods to implement a directory scan independent of\nfilp which could be shared with nfs export funtionality.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nChange-Id: I9cd8413a126ec1ea45fa5c73228e9b711e1e83a6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
